{"TopicId":141828,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Wrong Rung","CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-15T03:22:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-15T03:22:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe need for a procedural ladder type has already been suggested and this idea is something similar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe rungs that are part of the Z4k battery do not function; kerbals cannot grab hold of the rung.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf this type of rung was available on more parts but instead allow a kerbal to hold onto.the rung, allows for more ladder options..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00225y1um6S.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/5y1um6S.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe rungs on the Hitchhiker and the Materials Processing Lab work as ladders.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022T7IZRkX.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/T7IZRkX.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe more parts should have rungs integrated.\u00A0 An option to hide/remove them from the Part Action menu in the VAB/SPH only.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-15T22:29:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suspect that the rungs on the battery weren\u0027t meant to be functional.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill, we\u0027ll have to wait and see how the rumored rocket parts revamp turns out before determining whether it is appropriate to add rungs to batteries.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-16T20:11:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222632621\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141828\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466029791\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suspect that the rungs on the battery weren\u0027t meant to be functional.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat sounds fishy.\u00A0 Why are they there at all, in the exactly right place?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe should file a bug.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-16T20:12:04Z\u0022 title=\u002206/16/2016 08:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Corona688\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-16T20:19:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222633949\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141828\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466107889\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222511\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Corona688\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Corona688 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat sounds fishy.\u00A0 Why are they there at all, in the exactly right place?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDecorative elements?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-16T20:27:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222633960\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141828\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466108393\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDecorative elements?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe \u003Cstrong\u003Ehave\u003C/strong\u003E decorative ladders all over the place in the KSP grounds, just there for the heck of it, and you can climb them.\u00A0 Why those useless ones and not these useful ones?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBug, I call it, or design problem.\u00A0 Their engine may have problems with the notion of a 1-rung ladder.\u00A0 Which ladder are they climbing when they\u0027re crossing three at once?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy suggestion, either fix the rungs or convert them to some other widget so we can put our own rungs there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-16T20:28:11Z\u0022 title=\u002206/16/2016 08:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Corona688\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}